Dr Sergi Santos has said that his doll Samantha can decide she doesn’t want to have sex when she feels her lover is being aggressive, touched in a disrespectful manner or she is bored with the attention coming from her partner. A special robot, Samantha can talk dirty, play a romantic, act as a family, or go “extra naughty” once the settings are switched on. She also has hands, hips and face that can be stimulated if done properly. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-677968 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Samantha-sex-doll-with-Inventor-Dr-Sergi-Santos.-Photo-Jordi-Perez-Donat-Barcroft-Images.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="798" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Samantha-sex-doll-with-Inventor-Dr-Sergi-Santos.-Photo-Jordi-Perez-Donat-Barcroft-Images.jpg 634w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Samantha-sex-doll-with-Inventor-Dr-Sergi-Santos.-Photo-Jordi-Perez-Donat-Barcroft-Images-487x389.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Samantha-sex-doll-with-Inventor-Dr-Sergi-Santos.-Photo-Jordi-Perez-Donat-Barcroft-Images-301x240.jpg 301w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Samantha-sex-doll-with-Inventor-Dr-Sergi-Santos.-Photo-Jordi-Perez-Donat-Barcroft-Images-601x480.jpg 601w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Samantha-sex-doll-with-Inventor-Dr-Sergi-Santos.-Photo-Jordi-Perez-Donat-Barcroft-Images-600x479.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /> According to DailyMail, the invention was created with Dr Santos’s wife Maritsa Kissamitaki who he said might not be in the mood to have sex sometimes. Dr Sentos says that she has helped his marriage. “So if I have the doll, I’ll not divorce because of sex – in my case, I think that’s good enough”. Meanwhile, there will be a mass production of the doll soon for a retail price of £3,600 (N1,711,885). Must be some good loving she is giving.. Read More: Nigerian Twitter Divided Over New Sex Doll